1
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:20,840
Ting.

2
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,600
Be the tail player for me.

3
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:32,840
Ugh. But I don't like that stuff, Sis.

4
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,880
You can do it yourself.

5
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:37,920
What if we get hired?
Then we could use the money to help Dad.

6
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,160
Can't you just help me?

7
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,680
I have my own ways of making money too.

8
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:57,040
<i>Alright, focus.</i>

9
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,760
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

10
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,720
The eyes!

11
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,840
The lips. Yeah, beautiful!

12
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,400
Yeah.

13
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,800
Strong.

14
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:10,039
Stable.

15
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:12,280
Delicate. Delicate.

16
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,400
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

17
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,640
Not too fast.

18
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,320
Are you messing with me?

19
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,160
Take it easy. Don't get on my nerves.

20
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,560
Slowly. Start over!

21
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:31,240
Hold on. Are you doing this on purpose?

22
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:33,000
More force, just enough to sound good!

23
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,800
Yeah.

24
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,640
Eyes! Okay, wonderful.

25
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,760
Stable.

26
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,560
‪That's it.

27
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,520
‪Alright.

28
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,760
Awesome.

29
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,680
You catch on fast, Taew.

30
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,080
Did you practice in secret?

31
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:02,280
I've taught her
since she was a little girl.

32
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:05,080
Why would you teach her that?

33
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,520
- What?
- Don't you remember?

34
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,680
Lit didn't want you to.

35
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:11,440
I taught her kung fu, not lion dancing.

36
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:14,480
After she learned kung fu,
her body got stronger.

37
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:17,400
Then lion dancing became easy.

38
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,600
Well…

39
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:25,240
If that's the case,
who's going to play the tail for her?

40
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,560
I'll do it.

41
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,960
Kla!

42
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:39,080
How could you? It's not good
to play the tail for a woman.

43
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:42,200
With skills like yours,
you should be the head.

44
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,280
Dad.

45
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,040
I have the strongest foundation.

46
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,200
When Taew performs,

47
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,400
I'll be the one backing her up.

48
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:10,200
‪KIMHAN

49
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,000
‪Okay.

50
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,880
Left.

51
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,920
Right.

52
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:11,000
Let's go!

53
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:15,920
What? Uncle Don.

54
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,600
What's wrong? Why aren't you turning too?

55
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,400
Ugh. I can't remember that.

56
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,160
I'm 50 years old now.
I'm here to perform the lion dance,

57
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,360
not to do moves like that.

58
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,200
Well, this is <i>Mor Lam Sing</i>.
It needs new moves.

59
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,440
Screw <i>Mor Lam Sing</i>.

60
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,520
Dancing around like an idiot?
Anyone else can do it, but I'm not.

61
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,720
Take it back.

62
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,280
You too. You're a grown-up,

63
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,960
yet you keep spoiling the kids.

64
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,760
Look, the world has changed.

65
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,080
You have to change with it too.

66
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,960
"The Knower of the Worlds,"
you understand?

67
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,480
World Wide Web.

68
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,240
I don't know what you're talking about.
What World Wide Web?

69
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,800
- Dad.
- Uncle Don.

70
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,960
- Uncle Don.
- Don't call me.

71
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,040
Sai.

72
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,600
Don't worry about it.

73
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,280
I'll talk to him.

74
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,800
Old Man, I apologize on Dad's behalf.

75
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,360
I didn't take it to heart.

76
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,720
Idiot.

77
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,880
Hey, it's almost time for work.

78
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:18,880
Yeah, I totally forgot.

79
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,280
Old Man, I'll stop practicing
for today, okay?

80
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,680
Okay, okay. Go to work. Go.

81
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,160
- I'm off, Old Man.
- Yeah, go ahead.

82
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,560
- Put everything away.
- Yes.

83
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,960
Don't overthink it.

84
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,120
<i>Guys,</i>

85
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,200
<i>- look at this. We're innocent,</i>
<i>- Stop filming!</i>

86
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:53,400
<i>but they arrested us.</i>

87
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,560
<i>- We're innocent.</i>
<i>- Why are you filming?!</i>

88
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:58,080
<i>She's a bold-faced liar.</i>
<i>Everyone, remember her face.</i>

89
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,920
<i>She sent people to harass us…</i>

90
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,040
Don't forget to blur the faces.

91
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,840
- <i>Look at her. It's this bitch.</i>
- Ugh.

92
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,640
No need to blur their faces.

93
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,960
These corrupt cops and businesses

94
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,680
need to be exposed so society knows.

95
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:12,200
This video is gonna get a lot of views.

96
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,360
CLASHING FOR JUSTICE

97
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:18,440
UPLOADING VIDEO

98
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,920
PROCESSING SOON

99
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:23,800
PHAETPANYA GENERAL HOSPITAL

100
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,640
He's in cardiac arrest.

101
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,200
One dose of adrenaline.

102
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,680
CPR.

103
00:07:57,240 --> 00:08:01,080
Taew, the hospital called and said
Dad's blood pressure had dropped.

104
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,840
<i>His pulse is slowing down too.</i>

105
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,040
<i>They said we should get there immediately.</i>

106
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,640
Thank you so much.

107
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,880
Mom, what's wrong with Dad?

108
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,040
It's nothing serious, but

109
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,520
I'm transferring Dad to another hospital.

110
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,919
- You're transferring him?
- Mm.

111
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,720
He's in serious condition.
Which hospital would admit him, Mom?

112
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,960
I found a hospital
with top-tier neurologists for you.

113
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:44,680
Once the paperwork is done,
we can move him.

114
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,040
That's right, Sis.

115
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:52,920
Thank you.

116
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,280
You're welcome.

117
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,200
But don't worry too much.

118
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,760
If anyone else needs my help,

119
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,800
I'll be there too.

120
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,040
Easy, Mom.

121
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,960
This hospital is so luxurious.

122
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,920
I doubt they even accept
the Universal Coverage scheme.

123
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,240
Whether they accept it or not,
I'll find the money to pay for it, Mom.

124
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,880
If it's not enough,
I'll use the land to get a bank loan.

125
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,920
Will the bank let you take out a loan?

126
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:41,160
Last time, Dad still
borrowed money from Kamnan Danai.

127
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,240
Mom.

128
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,520
We have to try everything we can.

129
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,080
I believe there has to be a way out.

130
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,360
Taew.

131
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,680
Kla.

132
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,160
I tried calling you.

133
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,760
I'm busy
dealing with Dad's hospital transfer.

134
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,800
I was just about to call you.

135
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,960
But how did you and Sai find me?

136
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:13,440
Ting called and told me

137
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:16,200
that Mr. Natee brought Uncle Lit here.

138
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,440
Taew, did you know?

139
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,760
This hospital belongs to Chairman Pinyo.

140
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:29,240
Mr. Natee.

141
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,640
This was your plan, wasn't it?

142
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:36,880
You're tricking us
into selling our land to you.

143
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,720
Seriously, let me ask you.

144
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,360
What's your relationship
with Chairman Pinyo?

145
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,320
Huh?

146
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:52,080
I'm just a company employee
who does a good job,

147
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,280
so Mr. Pinyo trusts me.

148
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,520
Kla.

149
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,360
Kla.

150
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,560
Come here.

151
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,520
Come on.

152
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,960
- Hey.
- Why did you drag me here?

153
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,680
Kla, just calm down.

154
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,800
You always think too negatively.

155
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,680
Mr. Natee has helped us
with a lot of things,

156
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,480
and he said
it has nothing to do with buying the land.

157
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,880
Look at him, Sai.

158
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,720
He's no better than Ms. Ploy.

159
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,160
Honestly,
I think he's even worse than her.

160
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:36,480
Sai, don't you see? He's just
buttering Taew up to let her guard down.

161
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,640
Then he'll buy our land.

162
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,200
Don't be so naive.

163
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,960
That's why they think
Isan people are so gullible.

164
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,640
Kla.

165
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:49,800
I'm not stupid enough
to let anyone fool me that easily.

166
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,760
Before I brought my dad here,

167
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,000
I looked into it,

168
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,520
and the doctors here are experts
in treating brain disorders.

169
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,520
Also,

170
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:00,080
if I knew where my dad could be cured,

171
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,800
I'd take him anywhere.

172
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:03,680
Can you please calm down?

173
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:09,240
Why didn't you tell me
that Chairman Pinyo owns this hospital?

174
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,240
I didn't think I needed to,

175
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,440
since our main goal

176
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:19,240
is to find a skilled neurologist
for your father.

177
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,280
And no matter who owns this place,

178
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,880
I would still recommend
that you transfer your father here.

179
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,600
And I'm certainly not so despicable

180
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,400
as to use someone's life
as a bargaining chip for business.

181
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,600
Excuse me.

182
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:38,000
Are you Mr. Chalit Kaenthaisong's family?

183
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,280
- Yes.
- The doctor needs to see you now.

184
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,280
- Doctor, Mr. Chalit's family is here.
- Okay.

185
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,640
I've already examined him.

186
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,680
The reason he still hasn't woken up

187
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:06,040
might be due to

188
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,560
blood pooling
in a critical area of the brain,

189
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,240
or brain swelling.

190
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,440
If we leave it untreated,
it could be life-threatening.

191
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:16,200
Does that mean

192
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,560
Dad has to have another surgery?

193
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:22,560
Yes, but it's a fifty-fifty chance,

194
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,520
because he has been unresponsive
for several days now.

195
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,040
So does that mean…

196
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:31,080
my husband could die, Doctor?

197
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,840
It's possible.

198
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,520
Or if he survives,

199
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,560
he may not fully recover.

200
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:42,480
But if we don't operate now,
there's a high risk he won't make it.

201
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,880
Then please operate, Doctor.

202
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,160
Alright.

203
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,400
Hello, Dad.

204
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:13,200
<i>I heard you claimed I ordered Mr. Chalit</i>
<i>to be transferred to our hospital?</i>

205
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:15,080
No one would touch a case this risky.

206
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,680
If he dies and his family sues us,

207
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,520
it will ruin our hospital's reputation.

208
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,240
I'm sorry, Dad.

209
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,760
But since his condition is so severe,

210
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:25,320
I went to consult Dr. Supot.

211
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,040
If we leave it any longer,
he might not make it.

212
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,040
And is that any of your business?

213
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:35,920
Well, don't you want his land?

214
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:44,720
And this family really values gratitude.

215
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,320
If we can save him,

216
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,320
they might change their minds
about the land.

217
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,800
I need to go.

218
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,680
Why did you sneak off to take a call?

219
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,960
Or maybe…

220
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,720
you're hiding something?

221
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,320
It's normal, isn't it?

222
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:17,320
No one talks about personal matters
in front of strangers.

223
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:18,800
It's good manners.

224
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,960
And no one should eavesdrop
on someone else's call.

225
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,560
Because it's rude.

226
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,760
Honestly, I don't believe

227
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,880
that someone like you

228
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:37,440
would help someone
without expecting anything in return.

229
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:39,920
If I find out

230
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,680
you're plotting against Taew,

231
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,680
I'll destroy you.

232
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,920
NATEE PITIPANICHCHAROENPAN

233
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:01,520
NATEE PITIPANICHCHAROENPAN

234
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,920
NATEE BOONPIMAI
MANAGEMENT TRAINEE

235
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,200
Boonpimai?

236
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:10,920
Natee Boonpimai.

237
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,520
He's just a trainee, huh?

238
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,320
He acts like the company's heir.

239
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,240
Or is he related to the chairman?

240
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,000
Blade.

241
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,760
Gauze, please.

242
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,520
Hey, my channel's going viral!

243
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:05,920
Kamnan…

244
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,359
- Hey!
- What?

245
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,400
Stop!

246
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,119
Let me go!

247
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,600
What did I ever do to you?

248
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,000
Delete my video now

249
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,000
if you don't want to die.

250
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,080
You won't get away with this.

251
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:43,320
You want to disappear without a trace?

252
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,040
I don't know. Your parents might be happy.

253
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,680
You're just a worthless brat

254
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:53,760
living off your parents' money.

255
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:55,600
- Yeah…
- Take that!

256
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:05,360
Hey!

257
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,760
You can either keep it,

258
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,800
or… delete it right now.

259
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:35,040
Don't!

260
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,000
Hey!

261
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:38,640
Hey, don't do it!

262
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,880
I give up! I give up.

263
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,040
- Ting.
- I'll delete it.

264
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:52,800
It's deleted.

265
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,760
That's it.

266
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:01,840
What did you do to my brother?

267
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,440
Sis!

268
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,600
Sis!

269
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,280
Sis!

270
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:37,520
That's enough.

271
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,960
I was just threatening him.

272
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:45,360
From now on, stay away from me.

273
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,520
As for you,

274
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:50,920
if you still won't sell the land
to the Kamnan,

275
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,160
things will only get worse for you.

276
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:06,480
So that's why they beat you up.

277
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,720
You know the cops are on their side.

278
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,800
You're gonna get charged
under the Computer Crime Act.

279
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:13,880
Ugh, how was I supposed to know?

280
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,440
I just wanted justice for us.

281
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,640
It's just a video of a fight.

282
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,560
You can't use that as evidence.

283
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,160
If something happened to you,
Mom would be worried sick.

284
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,120
If you want to help me,

285
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,600
then focus on studying
so you can help me out.

286
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,560
Get inside.

287
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,880
Oh, wait. Where are you going?

288
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,200
Let's go together.

289
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,720
I'm going to work.

290
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,200
Ugh, Sis.

291
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,760
You got beaten up like this,
and you're still going?

292
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:44,440
Can't you take a day off?

293
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:46,880
Interest doesn't take days off.

294
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,320
Sis.

295
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,040
Then let's sell the land,

296
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,480
so we'll have money to treat Dad

297
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:57,840
and pay off our debt.

298
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,680
We'd still have some left over to save.

299
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:03,120
Ting.

300
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,640
I will never sell it.

301
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,840
Okay, then just wait
until everyone's dead.

302
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:35,320
Taew, I'm sorry.

303
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,640
If I hadn't let Ting
post the video on social media,

304
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,600
you wouldn't have gotten hurt like this.

305
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,080
It's okay, Sai. Even without the video,

306
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,200
they were already trying
to pick a fight with us anyway.

307
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,320
Taew.

308
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,240
But I'm sure

309
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,600
the broken pole and ruined drum

310
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,240
were definitely their doing.

311
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,640
They probably think
that without Uncle Lit,

312
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,840
Aunt Yao will sell them the land.

313
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:14,360
From now on,
be careful wherever you go, okay?

314
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:23,560
Don't forget
to take your anti-inflammatory medicine

315
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,960
so you'll get better soon.

316
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:46,960
I have no idea when Dad will wake up.

317
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:51,200
But the doctor at the hospital said

318
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:53,640
the surgery went well.

319
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:57,360
Right now,
I want you to calm down a little, okay?

320
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,120
The doctors are really good too.

321
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,360
Just like Mr. Natee said.

322
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,080
Mr. Natee is a good man, right?

323
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,480
He's helped us from the very beginning.

324
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:19,960
<i>Taew.</i>

325
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,760
<i>You've been working so hard for so long.</i>

326
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:26,240
<i>Uncle Lit is like a father to me.</i>

327
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:30,040
<i>It's time for me to repay his kindness.</i>

328
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,480
Start it.

329
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,480
Come on.

330
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,800
Grab my waist.

331
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,840
Hello, Ting. I'm right outside.

332
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,640
Natee.

333
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:25,120
Nobody knows
you came here to see me, right?

334
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:28,720
Nobody knows. Is something wrong, Natee?

335
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:33,400
I want to know what happened to Taew.

336
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:39,840
Hey.

337
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:42,320
What aren't you telling me?

338
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,600
Hey, don't forget

339
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,680
that we're partners now.

340
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:56,560
If anything happens,
tell me so we can deal with it in time.

341
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:02,720
I promise I won't tell anyone about this.

342
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:11,120
Ploy's men beat her up.

343
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,880
What happened? Why did they beat her up?

344
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,080
Have you filed a police report?

345
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,320
It was my fault.

346
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,800
Alright, it's round three,
the final round.

347
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:35,040
Red or blue,

348
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:37,280
pick your side. Let's go!

349
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,360
Go get him.

350
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:43,720
Whoa, blue.

351
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,840
Red throws a punch! A right hand!

352
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:49,680
‪Charge!

353
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,200
Red charges!

354
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,160
Red dodges! Guard up!

355
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:18,720
- Go!
- Get him!

356
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,640
- Get up!
- Go get him!

357
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,360
<i>I can't lose.</i>

358
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,080
<i>I need money to treat Uncle Lit.</i>

359
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,440
Round over!

360
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,000
She's a new singer, sir.

361
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:47,800
She's just trying out today.

362
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:55,080
She's good.

363
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:09,880
Keep it safe, Joi.

364
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:12,480
Lose it and you're dead, Joi.

365
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:13,640
This is a lot.

366
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,280
Pim, there you are.

367
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:18,440
Alright.

368
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:21,440
Thank you, Pim.

369
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:24,600
- I'll wash this dress for you.
- Sai.

370
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:28,960
Kamnan Danai wants
to see you in the VIP room.

371
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:32,320
I'm not going, Bee.

372
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,720
The Kamnan called for you.
How can you not go?

373
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:38,440
He's a VIP guest here at the club.

374
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:41,160
If you don't go,
you won't be allowed to sing here again.

375
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:44,160
Fine! I won't sing here!

376
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,920
If he wants it so badly,
you go to him yourself!

377
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,680
She's here to sell her voice and talent,
not her body.

378
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:51,160
If you want to go, then go.

379
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,680
- Yeah.
- We don't care.

380
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:54,880
- Let's go.
- Hey.

381
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,000
You can leave.

382
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,680
But this bitch isn't going anywhere yet.

383
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:02,720
Don't be afraid.

384
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:04,640
I'll protect you myself.

385
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,960
Joi, are you sure?

386
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:08,200
Are you asking for it?

387
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,960
You're dead!

388
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:38,240
SRIKHRAM KRAJANGFAH

389
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:39,480
Hey.

390
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,720
- Give it back!
- Go.

391
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:42,880
- You bastard!
- Hey.

392
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,400
- My mom called. Give it here!
- Go!

393
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,760
Keep walking.

394
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:46,960
SRIKHRAM KRAJANGFAH

395
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,400
Yao.

396
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:54,760
Have you seen Sai?

397
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:57,760
I saw her leave already.

398
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,840
No, she still hasn't come back yet.

399
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:03,160
I've called her so many times,
and she keeps hanging up on me.

400
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,560
Normally, at this hour,

401
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:06,360
she never goes anywhere.

402
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:09,840
- I'm really worried.
- Calm down.

403
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:12,560
Maybe she came back to hang out with Taew.

404
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,920
Should we go upstairs and check?

405
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,960
- Yeah, let's go.
- Let's go.

406
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:57,320
AUNT SRIKHRAM

407
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:09,640
- Taew, are you asleep yet, honey?
- Taew.

408
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:11,640
- Taew.
- Yes, Mom?

409
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:17,720
- Taew.
- What is it, Mom? Auntie?

410
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,200
Is Sai with you, Taew?

411
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,240
No, she's not.

412
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:25,360
I don't know when she left. I fell asleep.

413
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:26,320
What's wrong?

414
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,080
Where is Sai at this hour?

415
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:33,160
She hasn't read my texts
since this evening.

416
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:34,680
Yao.

417
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,520
It's okay. Don't worry.

418
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,480
We'll help you find her, okay?

419
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:41,720
I'll go tell the others to look for her.

420
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:44,200
Thanks, Taew.

421
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:46,040
- Let's go, Yao.
- Let's go.

422
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:47,240
Come on.

423
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,960
Where are you, Sai?

424
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:04,080
Thanks.

425
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:10,800
I saw you at Mr. Chalit's house, right?

426
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:13,520
Did you call for me, Kamnan?

427
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,560
Move over so she can sit.

428
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:20,400
Come sit here, honey.

429
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:26,920
Go ahead. The Kamnan called you.

430
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,280
Thank you so much.

431
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:36,960
What would you like to eat?
You can order whatever you want.

432
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:38,080
Let me treat you.

433
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:40,560
I'm not hungry.

434
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,400
What is it you want, Kamnan?

435
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,840
So I can get back to work.

436
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:50,120
I saw you helping your mom
sell rice noodles.

437
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,160
Right?

438
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,400
So why are you here singing?

439
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:57,960
You want to earn some extra money?

440
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:02,680
Yes.

441
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,720
I'm helping Uncle Lit
pay off his debt to you.

442
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:07,640
With interest this high,

443
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,679
he can't survive without our help.

444
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:12,560
Good.

445
00:34:13,159 --> 00:34:14,960
I like grateful kids like you.

446
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:21,600
Pour her a glass of liquor, will you?

447
00:34:23,159 --> 00:34:24,480
Yes, Kamnan.

448
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:33,360
But singing like this,
how much can you really make a night?

449
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,040
Just come and keep me company.

450
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:37,760
Make me happy,

451
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:40,080
and I'll give you everything.

452
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:49,840
Sounds good?

453
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:12,520
Alright.

454
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:15,320
Finish this glass first, then you can go.

455
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:17,880
Consider it a gift.

456
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:38,160
Hey!

457
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,440
You bitch.

458
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:45,920
Remember this.

459
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,920
If someone like me
wants something, I get it.

460
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,320
Take her to the safe house.

461
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,720
Let go! Let go of me!

462
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:58,640
Let go of me! Let go!

463
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:02,320
Help! Let go!

464
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:11,960
KLA

465
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:30,400
Fifty thousand.

466
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:31,840
Thank you so much.

467
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:34,280
Just let me know next time, okay?

468
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:38,560
If you keep fighting this well,

469
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,840
you've got it.

470
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:42,880
Thank you so much.

471
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,440
- Hello, Joi.
<i>- Hello.</i>

472
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:56,800
Kla, can you come help me?

473
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,560
Where are you, Joi?

474
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,360
Joi?

475
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:08,800
Seriously, where are you?

476
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:22,200
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
